"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Quick Start with Python\\n\\nThis guide will walk you through the steps to set up and start using the dYdX API Python library.\\n\\n::::steps\\n\\n## Install Python3 and Poetry\\n\\nChoose and install [Python 3.9+](https://www.python.org/downloads/) and [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/docs#installing-with-the-official-installer) for your system.\\n\\n## Clone the dydx client repo\\n\\n```bash\\ngit clone https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-clients.git\\n```\\n\\n## Install all dependencies\\n\\nGo to the Python client library.\\n\\n```bash\\ncd v4-clients/v4-client-py-v2\\n```\\n\\nInstall the project dependencies using the following command:\\n\\n```bash\\npoetry install\\n```\\n\\n## Run an example\\n\\nNow, we can run an example file. Let's run `example/accounts_endpoint.py` file.\\n\\n```bash\\npoetry run python -m examples.account_endpoints\\n```\\n\\n::::\\n\\n**Now, you can play around with all the available examples. Happy trading!**\\n\\n:::tip[Python Package]\\nThe Python client is also available through the PyPI [package](https://pypi.org/project/dydx-v4-client/) `dydx-v4-client`.\\n```bash [Installation]\\npip install dydx-v4-client\\n```\\n:::\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/interaction/client/quick-start-py#quick-start-with-python\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>This guide will walk you through the steps to set up and start using the dYdX API Python library.</p>\\n<div data-vocs-steps=\\\"true\\\"><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/client/quick-start-py.mdx#quick-start-with-python\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nThis guide will walk you through the steps to set up and start using the dYdX API Python library.\\n\",\"title\":\"Quick Start with Python\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/client/quick-start-py#install-python3-and-poetry\",\"html\":\"<p>Choose and install <a href=\\\"https://www.python.org/downloads/\\\">Python 3.9+</a> and <a href=\\\"https://python-poetry.org/docs#installing-with-the-official-installer\\\">Poetry</a> for your system.</p></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/client/quick-start-py.mdx#install-python3-and-poetry\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Choose and install Python 3.9+ and Poetry for your system.\",\"title\":\"Install Python3 and Poetry\",\"titles\":[\"Quick Start with Python\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/client/quick-start-py#clone-the-dydx-client-repo\",\"html\":\"<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">git</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> clone</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-clients.git</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/client/quick-start-py.mdx#clone-the-dydx-client-repo\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"git clone https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-clients.git\",\"title\":\"Clone the dydx client repo\",\"titles\":[\"Quick Start with Python\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/client/quick-start-py#install-all-dependencies\",\"html\":\"<p>Go to the Python client library.</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">cd</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> v4-clients/v4-client-py-v2</span></span></code></pre><p>Install the project dependencies using the following command:</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">poetry</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> install</span></span></code></pre></div><div data-depth=\\\"2\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/client/quick-start-py.mdx#install-all-dependencies\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Go to the Python client library.cd v4-clients/v4-client-py-v2Install the project dependencies using the following command:poetry install\",\"title\":\"Install all dependencies\",\"titles\":[\"Quick Start with Python\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/client/quick-start-py#run-an-example\",\"html\":\"<p>Now, we can run an example file. Let&#x27;s run <code>example/accounts_endpoint.py</code> file.</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">poetry</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> run</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> python</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> -m</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> examples.account_endpoints</span></span></code></pre></div></div>\\n<strong>Now, you can play around with all the available examples. Happy trading!</strong>\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"tip\\\"><strong data-callout-title=\\\"true\\\">Python Package</strong><p>The Python client is also available through the PyPI <a href=\\\"https://pypi.org/project/dydx-v4-client/\\\">package</a> <code>dydx-v4-client</code>.</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\" data-title=\\\"Installation\\\" data-lang=\\\"bash\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">pip</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> install</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> dydx-v4-client</span></span></code></pre></aside>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/client/quick-start-py.mdx#run-an-example\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Now, we can run an example file. Let&#x27;s run example/accounts_endpoint.py file.poetry run python -m examples.account_endpoints\\nNow, you can play around with all the available examples. Happy trading!\\nPython PackageThe Python client is also available through the PyPI package dydx-v4-client.pip install dydx-v4-client\",\"title\":\"Run an example\",\"titles\":[\"Quick Start with Python\"]}]}}"
